Filter Reports by Values

To filter a report by value, select a field from the Add dropdown menu or picklist. 
Choose Field Filter to filter on fields, such as Account Name equals Acme.
Personalize field filters for user fields like Account Owner or Created By.
Restrict results to the currently signed-in user with relative values.

Filter Logic requires at least one field filter and is used to customize how existing filters apply to your report. 
Use AND (OR) logic to combine multiple filters, such as Filter 1 AND (Filter 2 OR Filter 3).

Cross Filter to filter on one objectâ€™s relationship to another object. 
Add a subfilter to further filter by the second object.

Row Limit to limit the number of report results in tabular reports.
Enter filter criteria and optionally lock field filters while viewing a report in Lightning Experience.
Click Save and Run Report to view your filtered report.

Each report supports up to 20 field filters.
title: Filtering Reports in Salesforce
